07/21/2022,748.1101(b)(1)(B) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/29/2022,12/08/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,Investigation by DFPS found that a child in care was exploited by a staff member to obtain and distribute illegal drugs.  ,"12.8.22-Inspection conducted at Sweeten Home.  Three staff were interviewed regarding the recent boundaries training and subsequent changes in policies and procedures and all provided details of the trainings and subsequent changes as a result. Staff have already begun new cell phone monitoring procedures and a copy was provided of a completed cell phone monitoring report.

12.7.22-Administrator provided via email training forms for each staff member showing that staff received training on boundaries as well as the updated policies and procedures as discussed on 12.2.2212.

12.2.22-Administrator provided via email updated policies and procedures for monitoring electronic devices, the new monitoring electronic devices policy and cell phone monitoring report, updated telephone policy, and new training form Professional Boundaries with Children Living in Residential Child Care. This training will include the review of the Telephone Policy and Monitoring Electronic Devices Policy as well.  

11.30.22-CCR inspector spoke with Administrator by phone as well as email on this date regarding the child's rights deficiency.  Administrator confirmed that SWI was contacted as soon as the inappropriate text messages were discovered and perpetrator was immediately banned from access to the physical premises as well as any electronic means of communicating with the children in care, including a safety plan that temporarily removed all electronics from children and not allowing children to go off campus unless accompanied by staff.  Administrator is actively considering a variety of available resources regarding appropriate boundaries between staff and children in residential care that he will begin immediately reviewing with administrative staff and house supervisors in weekly meetings, and these staff will in turn begin communicating these with their direct care staff while a formal training curriculum is developed.  Sweeten Home currently has an electronic device policy that children acknowledge during placement that allows staff to monitor their cell phone usage,and Sweeten Home will continue to require cell phones to be turned in overnight, with monthly cell phone monitoring for inappropriate content to be mandatory for every child in care going forward rather than on a random selection basis as they have done in the past.  Children will be provided with the landline phone numbers for their house as well as their supervisor's cell phone number as their initial points of contact at placement. 

"
