06/22/2022,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/19/2022,08/16/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"1 staff member who was on duty consumed an alcoholic beverage. 2 other staff members who were volunteering their time, but still around children in care, also consumed an alcoholic beverage. ","The administrator emailed and spoke on the phone with the Inspector to discuss the follow up plan. The three staff members were given written verbal warnings as soon as the operation became aware of the incident.  Verbal written warnings were dated 3/14/2022 and each staff member was told that they are not to consume any alcohol while they are on duty on campus or off campus. Volunteers/Off-duty staff cannot be responsible for supervising children while consuming alcohol beverages. 
For future trips, Sweeten Home for Children has taken other measures during lengthy off campus trips (more than 72 hours) that allow staff to have personal time off which includes providing separate housing for staff who are ""off the clock"".  When staff are ""off the clock"" they are not responsible for supervising children and are free to conduct themselves as they normally would during ""off time"".  All staff are aware when they are ""on duty"" or around children, no alcoholic beverages can be consumed.     "
05/18/2022,748.2605(b)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,07/07/2022,06/27/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,A child was in a prone position during a restraint. The restraint lasted for about 6-10 minutes. ,"Administrator Scott Russell emailed Inspector Jordan Green the following actions taken: 
The three employees that were involved and/or witnessed the physical restraint on Damari received written warnings. (These are attached to the email and will be entered into digital storage.) We reviewed physical restraint policies and procedures regarding prone restraints and time limits for transitional holds.  These employees understand that prone restraints are not permitted beyond one-minute transitional hold and that the child should have been transitioned into a sitting or standing basket hold restraint within one minute of implementing the prone restraint.  
Further follow-up on 6/29/22: Also, the operation has Restraint Training coming up again for all staff in late August.  Christy Lewis is certified in Peaceful Intervention and we plan to begin training staff in this Restraint Process starting in August as well. By having a certified Restraint person on staff, we feel that we will be able to enhance our Restraint Training Program and continue to reduce the need for Physical Restraints.  "
